title: Great Train Robbery.mp3
description:
The 1963 Great Train Robbery continues to hold a fascination for British people, even though there have been bigger robberies since.

This documentary looks back at the robbery and includes extensive interviews with the leader of the robbers Bruce Reynolds -  his last interview before he died - and with a now mute (after several strokes) Ronnie Biggs. Reynolds in particular comes across as an interesting character, but gives nothing away about the whereabouts of the money (he claims all his has long gone) or the identities of those who were never caught.
